# .handoff_bots — pluggable roster for handoff_bots.sh (copy to .handoff_bots, edit).
# One bot per line:  <name> | <pgrep_pattern> | <inbox_file> | <launch_command>
#   pgrep_pattern / inbox_file / launch_command may be '-' to skip that capability.
#   launch_command is eval'd — supply whatever spawns a session in YOUR environment
#   (Windows Terminal, tmux, screen, ssh, a launcher script…). The plugin only delegates.
#
# Windows Terminal example:
# docs  | monitor_inbox .*_inbox_docs | /proj/_inbox_docs.md | wt new-tab --title docs bash -lc 'cd /proj && claude'
# tmux example:
# build | node .*build-agent            | /proj/_inbox_build.md | tmux new-session -d -s build 'cd /proj && claude'
# status-only (no launch here):
# remote| ssh.*remote-agent             | /proj/_inbox_remote.md | -
